A man who poached three rhinos in South Africa has been sentenced to seventy-seven years in prison -one of the heaviest penalties for such a crime.
Mandla Chauke shot dead the rhino calves in Kruger National Park in 2011.
During the raid, shooting broke out between the poachers and park rangers -one of Chauke's accomplices was killed, and the poacher was found guilty of his murder.
An official from the South African National Parks Board welcomed the sentence, saying the courts had recognised the negative impact poaching had on wildlife and an economy dependent on tourism.
Seorang pria yang melakukan perburuan tiga ekor badak di Afrika Selatan dijatuhi hukuman penjara 77 tahun, salah satu hukuman terberat untuk kasus perburuan.
Mandla Chauke menembak mati anak-anak badak di Taman Nasional Kruger pada 2011.
Saat dilakukan penggerebekan pecah baku tembak antara para pemburu dan petugas taman yang membuat salah seorang kaki tangan Chauke tewas, dan Chauke dinyatakan bersalah atas kematian anak buahnya tersebut.
Seorang pejabat di Dewan Taman Nasional Afrika Selatan menyambut baik vonis ini, dengan mengatakan pengadilan telah mengakui dampak buruk perburuan di alam liar dan bahwa ekonomi (Afrika Selatan) tergantung dengan pariwisata.
The doctor fighting the deadly Ebola virus in Sierra Leone has himself contracted the disease.
Sheik Umar Khan was hailed as a national hero for his efforts to control the outbreak that has killed at least 200 people in the country.
The government said Dr Khan, who had treated more than 100 victims, had been transferred to a ward run by medical charity MSF.
Nurses at the hospital where he was working, in the town of Kenema, have gone on strike, following the deaths of three of their colleagues from suspected cases of Ebola
Dokter yang memerangi virus mematikan Ebola di Sierra Leone terkena penyakit tersebut.
Sheik Umar Khan dianggap sebagai pahlawan nasional atas upayanya mengatasi wabah yang sudah menewaskan setidaknya 200 orang di negara ini.
Pemerintah mengatakan Dr Khan, yang merawat lebih dari 100 korban, dipindahkan ke bangsal yang dijalankan oleh organisasi amal yang bergerak di bidang kesehatan, MSF.
Para perawat di rumah sakit tempat ia bekerja, di kota Kenema, mogok menyusul tewasnya tiga rekan kerja mereka diduga akibat terkena virus Ebola.
